decks.notes: This deck focuses on quickly ramping up mana to play big threats like Primeval Titan and combo pieces like Scapeshift. It utilizes Amulet of Vigor and various land cards to generate extra mana and make explosive plays. The deck aims to assemble the Amulet Titan combo by tutoring for key pieces with cards like Green Sun's Zenith and Urza's Saga. It also includes utility lands like Bojuka Bog and Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle to deal with graveyard strategies and burn opponents. Overall, the strategy revolves around efficiently assembling the combo pieces to overwhelm the opponent.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly fill up the graveyard with cards like Faithless Looting and Burning Inquiry to enable the casting of Hollow One and Detective's Phoenix for a fast and aggressive start. The deck also includes cards like Lightning Bolt and Fatal Push for removal, as well as Nihil Spellbomb for graveyard hate. The inclusion of cards like Inti, Seneschal of the Sun and Orcish Bowmasters provides additional value and disruption against opponents. This deck aims to overwhelm opponents with a combination of early threats and removal spells.

This deck aims to use the Underworld Breach combo to quickly fill the graveyard with artifacts and then repeatedly cast them from the graveyard to win the game. Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student are key pieces in filling up the graveyard while Mishra's Bauble and Mox Opal help generate mana. Urza's Saga helps to tutor for key combo pieces while Thassa's Oracle serves as an alternate win condition. Grinding Station and Malevolent Rumble provide additional ways to close out the game quickly.

This deck focuses on leveraging aggressive creatures while disrupting your opponent's game plan with cards that tax their resources. By combining creatures like Emperor of Bones and Overlord of the Balemurk with disruptive spells like Solitude and Ephemerate, you can control the board and apply pressure at the same time. A mix of removal spells like Fatal Push and Skyclave Apparition help deal with threats, while Aether Vial allows you to cheat creatures into play and maintain tempo. The deck aims to outvalue and outpace your opponent to secure victory.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on quickly establishing a board presence and pressuring the opponent with efficient creatures and burn spells. The deck utilizes cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury to attack the opponent's life total directly while also maintaining control with cards like Static Prison and Thraben Charm. With a mix of aggressive creatures and disruptive spells, the deck aims to close out games quickly and efficiently, overwhelming the opponent before they have a chance to stabilize.

The deck focuses on disrupting opponents' strategies while quickly putting pressure on them with aggressive creatures. It utilizes creatures with disruptive abilities like Aven Interrupter and Skyclave Apparition, along with powerful beaters like Overlord of the Balemurk and Solitude. The deck aims to control the board with cards like Fatal Push and Ephemerate, while using Aether Vial to cheat creatures into play quickly. By combining disruptive elements with aggressive threats, the deck aims to outpace and outmaneuver opponents in Modern 1 vs 1 matches.

The primary focus of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures and burn spells. Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, Guide of Souls, and Ocelot Pride provide early threats, while Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Seasoned Pyromancer generate additional value. Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury acts as a powerful finisher. Galvanic Discharge and Goblin Bombardment offer ways to deal direct damage to the opponent or their creatures. Static Prison helps control the board, while Arena of Glory provides additional combat tricks. The mana base includes a mix of fetch lands and dual lands to ensure consistent access to all colors.

The deck focuses on using ramp spells and mana acceleration to quickly bring out powerful Eldrazi creatures such as Emrakul and World Breaker to control the game. It also includes various spells and artifacts to disrupt the opponent's strategy and protect your own creatures. The deck aims to establish a strong board presence and overwhelm the opponent with high-powered threats while controlling the game with removal and disruption spells. Ultimately, the goal is to outvalue and outlast the opponent in a long game.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly mill the opponent's library using cards like Hedron Crab, Ruin Crab, Fractured Sanity, and Tasha's Hideous Laughter while disrupting them with spells like Archive Trap, Surgical Extraction, and Fatal Push. The deck also includes card draw spells like Visions of Beyond and Jace, the Perfected Mind to maintain resources. The strategy revolves around controlling the opponent's resources through milling and removing key cards from their graveyard to eventually win the game by milling them out completely.

This Amulet Titan deck focuses on quickly ramping up to play Primeval Titan and utilizing land combos to generate massive amounts of mana. The deck utilizes cards like Amulet of Vigor, Green Sun's Zenith, and Scapeshift to accelerate the land ramping process. With key lands like Urza's Saga and Boseiju, Who Endures, the deck can consistently search for the necessary pieces to pull off its powerful combos. The end goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a large number of powerful creatures and lands for a decisive victory.

This deck focuses on controlling the opponent's board through a combination of counterspells, removal spells, and hand disruption. By utilizing cards like Counterspell, Fatal Push, and Pest Control, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while maintaining card advantage. Additionally, the inclusion of Murktide Regent and Abhorrent Oculus provides a win condition through powerful threats. The mana base is streamlined to ensure consistency in casting the spells necessary for control. Overall, the deck seeks to outmaneuver the opponent and establish dominance through careful resource management and timely plays.

The main concept of this deck revolves around utilizing Hydroelectric Specimen and Thundertrap Trainer to generate a large amount of mana quickly. This mana is then used to cast spells like Goblin Charbelcher, Thassa's Oracle, and Jace, Wielder of Mysteries to win the game. The deck also includes a range of counterspells, control spells, and card draw options to protect the combo pieces and maintain consistency. The goal is to efficiently assemble the combo pieces and use them to overwhelm the opponent before they can respond.

The core strategy of this deck is to mill the opponent's deck as quickly as possible using cards like Hedron Crab, Ruin Crab, and Archive Trap. This is supported by disruption cards like Fatal Push, Drown in the Loch, and Surgical Extraction to disrupt the opponent's game plan. Visions of Beyond helps draw into more mill cards, while Tasha's Hideous Laughter can mill even more cards in one go. Jace, the Perfected Mind can provide additional milling and card advantage. The mana base is focused on fetching lands to ensure consistency in casting spells and activating abilities.

This deck focuses on aggressively deploying powerful creatures and dealing direct damage to the opponent using burn spells. The key strategy is to quickly establish a board presence with efficient creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Scion of Draco, and then finish off the opponent with Tribal Flames or Lightning Bolt. The inclusion of Leyline of the Guildpact and Leyline Binding helps to protect your creatures and disrupt the opponent's game plan. With a mix of both creatures and burn spells, this deck aims to overwhelm the opponent before they can stabilize.

This deck focuses on ramping up mana quickly to cast powerful spells such as Primeval Titan and Scapeshift. The key strategy is to utilize Amulet of Vigor to untap lands and generate additional mana, allowing for explosive plays with multiple land drops in a turn. By combining ramp spells like Arboreal Grazer and Explore with powerful lands like Urza's Saga and Lotus Field, the deck can assemble the necessary resources to overwhelm opponents with massive threats and combo finishes using Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle.

Utilizing powerful Eldrazi creatures and ramping up mana quickly, this deck aims to control the game through a combination of disruption and big threats. By quickly getting out Eldrazi like Emrakul, the Promised End and World Breaker, while also using cards like Kozilek's Return and Malevolent Rumble to control the board, this deck can overwhelm opponents before they have a chance to stabilize. The deck also utilizes artifacts and enchantments like Talisman of Curiosity and Utopia Sprawl to ramp up mana and ensure it can play its big threats ahead of schedule.

This control deck focuses on utilizing a mix of removal spells, countermagic, and card advantage to control the game and outvalue opponents. The deck includes powerful threats like Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student, supported by efficient removal spells like Path to Exile and Galvanic Discharge. Counterspell and Spell Snare provide protection and disruption, while Tune the Narrative and Orim's Chant help to control the opponent's actions. Wrath of the Skies acts as a board wipe, while the mana base allows for consistent access to all necessary colors of mana.
